body: Suppressor Suppressor() A class which can be used to silence output of function calls. ```python x = lambda : print("hello") x() # "hello" with fe.util.Suppressor() : x() # x() # "hello" ``` write write(self, dummy:str) -> None A function which is invoked during print calls. Args: dummy : The string which wanted to be printed.
title: Suppressor
